dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: The CIFAR-10 dataset contains 60,000 32x32 natural images with 10 classes. Previous contrastive learning methods have achieved highly accurate predictions on this dataset, and we utilize such a dataset mainly to illustrate the importance of Batch Norm in the encoder of transferring BiT models to SimSiam contrastive learning.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: P. Tschandl
C. Rosendahl
H. Kittler
dcterms:description: The medical image data used in this study is HAM10000, a publicly available dataset that consists of 10,015 dermatoscopic images from seven classes. Like most medical imaging datasets, HAM10000 is also highly imbalanced, where 67% of the data comes from nevi, 11% comes from melanoma, and the remaining 22% comes from the other five classes.
dcterms:title: HAM10000
